Create a single-file, self-contained web application (HTML, CSS, and JavaScript) named "Wide Multi-Gesture Radium Canvas" that allows users to draw in the air using their webcam and hand gestures. 

### Technology Stack
- Frontend: Vanilla HTML5, CSS3, and JavaScript.
- AI Tracking: Use MediaPipe Hands and Camera utilities via CDN:
  - https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@mediapipe/camera_utils/camera_utils.js
  - https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@mediapipe/hands/hands.js

### UI & Styling (CSS)
- Background: Pitch black (#080808) with a modern, centered dashboard layout.
- Container: A fixed 1024x768px rounded container holding the webcam video and a canvas layered precisely on top. Both elements must be horizontally mirrored (scaleX(-1)) for an intuitive user experience.
- Video Filter: Give the webcam feed a vibrant look by modifying opacity (0.65), brightness (1.4), contrast (1.25), and saturation (1.4).
- Control Bar: A floating, blurred glassmorphism menu bar at the top containing:
  - A "Radium Palette" color picker with neon presets (Neon Green #39FF14, Cyan #00FFFF, Magenta #FF00FF, Yellow #FFFF00).
  - A brush size range slider (6px to 60px).
  - A "Clear Canvas" button with a red neon hover glow.
  - A dynamic "Status Panel" pill text indicating the active mode with matching color accents.

### Core Visual Features (JavaScript Canvas)
- Ambient Effects: Continuously animate up to 60 flickering, diamond-shaped neon glitter particles drifting subtly in the background layer.
- Brush Glow: In drawing mode, lines should look like neon lights using canvas shadow attributes (`shadowBlur`, `shadowColor`) and `globalCompositeOperation = 'screen'` to make overlapping strokes look bright and radioactive.

### Gesture Control Logic (MediaPipe)
Process the first detected hand tracking the Index Finger Tip (Landmark 8) to map coordinates onto the canvas. Implement the following state machine based on finger extensions:
1. ☝ Draw Mode (Index finger extended; Middle, Ring, Pinky down): Draw continuous neon lines using the selected color and brush size. Ensure proper tracking vectors so lines don't break or jump erratically.
2. ✌ Laser Guide Mode (Index and Middle extended; Ring and Pinky down): Do not draw lines. Instead, project a subtle white dashed crosshair alignment grid (X and Y axes) intersecting at the finger tip. Reset the drawing vectors to avoid trailing lines.
3. ✋ Erase Mode (All 4 fingers fully extended): Act as an eraser using `globalCompositeOperation = 'destination-out'`. Display a circular dashed red boundaries indicator tracking the hand to show the eraser's radius.
4. ✊ Paused Mode (All fingers closed/fist): Cease all drawing and tracking updates.

Ensure the MediaPipe model initializes seamlessly with a minDetectionConfidence of 0.75, showing a "Loading AI..." status that flips to "Ready" once the camera feed kicks off.
